ish football|1973\u201374]]<ref name=\"MR20\">{{cite news |last1=Richards |first1=Alex |title=Leeds and England legend tests positive for coronavirus |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/breaking-leeds-england-legend-norman-21846053 |accessdate=10 April 2020 |publisher=Mirror Sport |date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Football League Second Division]]: [[1963-64 in English football|1963\u201364]]<ref name=\"GHIST\" />\n* [[FA Cup]]: [[1972 FA Cup Final|1972]];<ref name=\"NFM\" /> runners-up: [[1965 FA Cup Final|1965]],<ref>{{cite book |last1=Williams |first1=John |title=Red Men |date=April 2011 |publisher=Random House |page=116}}</ref> [[1970 FA Cup Final|1970]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Murray |first1=Scott |title=1970 FA Cup final replay |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2020/mar/21/chelsea-v-leeds-united-1970-fa-cup-final-replay-live |website=The Guardian |accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> [[1973 FA Cup Final|1973]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Norman Hunter relives 1973 final heartbreak against Sunderland |url=https://www.itv.com/news/calendar/2015-01-02/i-wanted-to-forget-that-day-norman-hunter-relives-1973-final-heartbreak/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |publisher=ITV News |date=2 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Football League Cup]]: [[1968 Football League Cup Final|1968]]<ref name=\"MR20\" />\n* [[FA Charity Shield]]: [[1969 FA Charity Shield|1969]];<ref name=\"BBC13\" /> runners-up: [[1974 FA Charity Shield|1974]]<ref>{{cite book |last1=Durham |first1=Adrian |title=Is he all that? |date=October 2013 |publisher=Simon & Schuster |page=159}}</ref>\n* [[Inter-Cities Fairs Cup]]: [[1968 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup Final|1968]], [[1971 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup Final|1971]];<ref name=\"BBC13\" /> runners-up: [[1967 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup Final|1967]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Inter-Cities Fairs Cup 1967 |url=http://www.mightyleeds.co.uk/matches/19670830.htm |website=Mighty Leeds |accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n* [[European Cup Winners' Cup]] runners-up: [[1973 European Cup Winners' Cup Final|1973]]<ref name=\"LLIVE\" />\n* [[European Cup]] runners-up: [[1975 European Cup Final|1975]]<ref name=\"ECF75\" />\n\n===Individual===\n* [[PFA Players' Player of the Year]]: [[PFA Players' Player of the Year|1973\u201374]]<ref name=\"NFM\" />\n* [[PFA Team of the Year]]: [[PFA Team of the Year|1973\u201374]]<ref>{{cite book |first=Tony |last=Lynch |title=The Official P.F.A. Footballers Heroes |year=1995 |publisher=Random House |location=London |isbn=978-0-09-179135-3}}</ref>\n* [[Football League 100 Legends]]: [[Football League 100 Legends|1998]]<ref name=\"BBC100\" />\n* Leeds United Player of the Year: [[List of Leeds United A.F.C. players#Player of the Year|1971]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Player of the Year |url=https://myleeds100.com/history/player-of-the-year/ |website=MyLeeds100 |publisher=Leeds United F.C. |accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{englandstats|529|name=Norman Hunter}}\n* {{Soccerbase manager|991|name=Norman Hunter}}\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n| title = England squads\n| bg = white\n| fg = #0B0B3F\n| bordercolor = #0B0B3F\n| list1 =\n{{England squad 1966 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{England squad UEFA Euro 1968}}\n{{England squad 1970 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n| title = Awards\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| list1 =\n{{1973\u201374 Football League First Division PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{PFA Players' Player of the Year}}\n{{Leeds United F.C. Player of the Year}}\n{{Bristol City F.C. Player of the Season}}\n{{Football League 100 Legends}}\n{{English Football Hall of Fame}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Managerial positions\n| list1 =\n{{Barnsley F.C. managers}}\n{{Rotherham United F.C. managers}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hunter, Norman}}\n[[Category:1943 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Gateshead]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:English football managers]]\n[[Category:Barnsley F.C. managers]]\n[[Category:Barnsley 