{"title_page": "Jesse Joronen", "text_new": "{{short description|Finnish professional footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Jesse Joronen\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Jesse Pekka Joronen\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|3|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Rautj\u00e4rvi]], Finland\n| height = 1.97 m\n| position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub = [[Brescia Calcio|Brescia]]\n| clubnumber = 1\n| youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20132009\n| youthclubs1 = Simpeleen Urheilijat\n| youthyears2 = 2009\n| youthclubs2 = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]\n| years1 = 2009\u20132017\n| clubs1 = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]\n| caps1 = 4\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2012\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Maidenhead United F.C.|Maidenhead United]] (loan)\n| caps2 = 8\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2013\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Cambridge United F.C.|Cambridge United]] (loan)\n| caps3 = 0\n| goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2013\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[FC Lahti]] (loan)\n| caps4 = 18\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2014\n| clubs5 = \u2192 [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] (loan)\n| caps5 = 4\n| goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2015\u20132016\n| clubs6 = \u2192 [[Stevenage F.C.|Stevenage]] (loan)\n| caps6 = 10\n| goals6 = 1\n| clubs7 = [[AC Horsens]]\n| caps7 = 28\n| goals7 = 0\n| years7 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs8 = [[F.C. Copenhagen|Copenhagen]]\n| caps8 = 37\n| goals8 = 0\n| years8 = 2018\u20132019\n| clubs9 = [[Brescia Calcio|Brescia]]\n| caps9 = 8\n| goals9 = 0\n| years9 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalyears1 = 2009\n| nationalteam1 = [[Finland national under-17 football team|Finland U17]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 6\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2010\n| nationalteam2 = [[Finland national under-19 football team|Finland U19]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 1\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2011\u20132014\n| nationalteam3 = [[Finland national under-21 football team|Finland U21]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 11\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2013\u2013\n| nationalteam4 = [[Finland national football team|Finland]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 8\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| club-update = 27 October 2019\n| ntupdate = 8 July 2018\n}}\n'''Jesse Pekka Joronen''' (born 21 March 1993) is a Finnish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Serie A]] club [[Brescia Calcio|Brescia]].<ref>[https://www.fck.dk/en/news/jesse-joronen-sold-brescia-calcio]\u201a fck.dk, 11 July 2019</ref> Joronen made his senior debut for [[Finland national football team|Finland]] in 2013.<ref name=\"intl\">{{cite news|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2013/january/24/joronens-finland-bow|title=Joronen's Finland Bow|date=24 January 2013|publisher=Fulham F.C.|accessdate=1 March 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Fulham===\nBorn and raised in the small town of Simpele located near the Russian border, Joronen joined [[Fulham F.C. Academy|Fulham Academy]] in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/Club/News/NewsArticles/2010/October/Joronen.aspx|title=Through The Ranks|publisher=Fulham Official Website|accessdate=19 April 2014|date=20 October 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101022160532/http://www.fulhamfc.com/Club/News/NewsArticles/2010/October/Joronen.aspx|archivedate=22 October 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref> In June 2010, Joronen signed his first professional contract with the club, which will keep him until 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/Club/News/NewsArticles/2010/June/PlayerContractRound-Up.aspx|title=Player Contract Round-Up |publisher= Fulham FC|date=1 June 2010|accessdate=19 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110608065801/http://www.fulhamfc.com/Club/News/NewsArticles/2010/June/PlayerContractRound-Up.aspx|archivedate=8 June 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2012, Joronen signed a two-year extension with Fulham, that will keep him until 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Suomalaismaalivahti jatkosopimukseen Fulhamin kanssa|url=http://www.mtv.fi/sport/jalkapallo/valioliiga/artikkeli/suomalaismaalivahti-jatkosopimukseen-fulhamin-kanssa/4014396|publisher=MTV.fi|language=Finnish|date=15 May 2012|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> Six month later, on 25 October 2012, Joronen joined [[Maidenhead United F.C.|Maidenhead United]] on loan<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.maidenhead-advertiser.co.uk/Sport/Football/Maidenhead-Utd-FC/Maidenhead-United-FC-sign-international-keeper-from-Fulham-25102012.htm|title=Maidenhead United FC sign international keeper from Fulham|date=25 October 2012|publisher=Maidenhead Advertiser|accessdate=1 March 2013}}</ref> and in February 2013, Joronen was loaned to [[Cambridge United F.C.|Cambridge United]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/21545766|title=Fulham keeper Jesse Joronen joins Cambridge United|date=22 February 2013|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=1 March 2013}}</ref> Only a day later Joronen returned to Fulham after he refused to be named as a substitute for Cambridge.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Sport/Cambridge-United/Cambridge-United-1-Hereford-United-3-23022013.htm |title=Cambridge United 1 Hereford United 3 |date=23 February 2013 |publisher=Cambridge News |accessdate=1 March 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103051228/http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Sport/Cambridge-United/Cambridge-United-1-Hereford-United-3-23022013.htm |archivedate= 3 January 2014 }}</ref>\n\nAfter a loan spell at Maidenhead United, Joronen then move back to Finland, where he joined Veikkausliiga side [[FC Lahti]] on loan until August.<ref>{{cite news|title=Joronen Fulhamista FC Lahteen \u2013 \"Haluan kehitty\u00e4 pelaajana\"|url=http://yle.fi/urheilu/joronen_fulhamista_fc_lahteen_-_haluan_kehittya_pelaajana/6618714|publisher=Yle Sports|language=Finnish|date=5 March 2013|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> After making eighteen appearance for the club, which he established himself as a first choice goalkeeper, Joronen returned to his parent club in early August.<ref>{{cite news|title=Englantiin palannut Jesse Joronen: \"FC Lahti ansaitsisi pronssin\"|url=http://www.suomifutis.com/2013/10/englantiin-palannut-jesse-joronen-fc-lahti-ansaitsisi-pronssin/|publisher=Soumi Futis.com|language=Finnish|date=14 October 2013|accessdate=27 December 2014}}<br>{{cite news|title=FC Lahti menett\u00e4\u00e4 ykk\u00f6svahtinsa|url=https://www.is.fi/veikkausliiga/art-2000000643261.html|publisher=Ilta-Sanomat|language=Finnish|date=28 July 2013|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nAt the start of the 2014\u201315 season, Joronen signed a two-year contract with the club that kept him until 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=New Deal For Jesse |url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2014/july/07/new-deal-for-jesse |publisher=Fulham F.C. |date=7 July 2014 |accessdate=27 December 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141227172903/http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2014/july/07/new-deal-for-jesse |archivedate=27 December 2014 |url-status=unfit }}</ref> He was then given his debut as the starting goalkeeper in Fulham's opening game in the [[Football League Championship|Championship]] against [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] on 9 August 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/28646535|title=Ipswich Town 2\u20131 Fulham|publisher=BBC Sport|date=9 August 2014|accessdate=21 November 2014}}</ref> After making three more appearance for the club, Joronen soon lost his first team place to [[Marcus Bettinelli]] and new goalkeeper signing, [[G\u00e1bor Kir\u00e1ly]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Fulham boss admits the club refused to buy a top keeper|url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/fulham-boss-admits-club-refused-7707322|publisher=Get West London|date=1 September 2014|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nJoronen joined [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] on loan for one month on 17 October 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29661972|title=Jesse Joronen: Fulham goalkeeper joins Accrington on loan|publisher=BBC Sport|date=17 October 2014|accessdate=21 November 2014}}</ref> Shortly after, he made his Accrington Stanley debut the next day, on 18 October 2014, starting in goal, in a 2\u20131 loss against Stevenage.<ref>{{cite news|title=FULL TIME: Stevenage 2 Accrington Stanley 1|url=http://www.lancashiretelegraph.co.uk/sport/11544716.FULL_TIME__Stevenage_2_Accrington_Stanley_1/|publisher=The Lancashire Telegraph|date=18 October 2014|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> However, after making three more appearance at Accrington Stanley whilst on loan, he returned early after dislocating his kneecap during a [[Football League Two|League Two]] match against [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Accrington Stanley captain Luke Joyce impressed with Shay McCartan's form|url=http://www.lancashiretelegraph.co.uk/sport/11577810.Accrington_Stanley_captain_Luke_Joyce_impressed_with_Shay_McCartan_s_form/|publisher=The Lancashire Telegraph|date=4 November 2014|accessdate=21 November 2014}}</ref> Then, it was announced that Joronen would be out for three to four months.<ref>{{cite news|title=Huuhkajavahti Jesse Joronen palaa kentille vasta ensi vuonna|url=http://www.sportti.com/uutinen.asp?CAT=3-3&ID=277013|publisher=Sportti.com|language=Finnish|date=3 November 2014|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 August 2015, Joronen signed for [[Stevenage F.C.|Stevenage]] on loan until January 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stevenage: Boro sign Jesse Joronen on loan from Fulham|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34078392|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 August 2015|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> He made his Stevenage debut two days later, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Super sub Hitchcock strikes to claim point at Dagenham and Redbridge|url=http://www.thecomet.net/sport/football/super-sub-hitchcock-strikes-to-claim-point-at-dagenham-and-redbridge-1-4213810|publisher=The Comet|date=29 August 2015|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> Joronen scored with a long-range clearance in a match against [[Wycombe Wanderers F.C.|Wycombe Wanderers]] on 17 October 2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/football-league/goalkeeper-jesse-joronen-scores-freak-long-range-goal-for-stevenage-from-just-outside-his-own-a6698206.html|title=Goalkeeper Jesse Joronen scores freak long-range goal for Stevenage from just outside his own penalty box|publisher=The Independent|date=17 October 2015|accessdate=17 October 2015}}</ref> He then kept his first clean sheet in a 3\u20130 win over [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]] in the first round of the FA Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stevenage 3 \u2013 0 Gillingham|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34685654|publisher=BBC Sport|date=7 November 2015|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> However, after making eleven appearance for the side, Joronen suffered an injury during the match against Gillingham and subsequently returned to his parent club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Yeovil Town preview: We have to be cautious but we are still going out to win this \"six-pointer\" says Teddy Sheringham|url=http://www.thecomet.net/stevenage-fc/yeovil-town-preview-we-have-to-be-cautious-but-we-are-still-going-out-to-win-this-six-pointer-says-teddy-sheringham-1-4310479|publisher=The Comet|date=13 November 2015|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> After returning to his parent club, Joronen signed a contract extension, keeping him until 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2016/may/12/jesse-joronen-extends-fulham-stay|title=Jesse Extends Fulham Stay|publisher=Fulham F.C.|accessdate=21 October 2017|date=12 May 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021193709/http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2016/may/12/jesse-joronen-extends-fulham-stay|archivedate=21 October 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2016\u201317 season, Joronen was featured three times in the EFL Cup, being the first choice goalkeeper ahead of Bettinelli.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fulham and the five things to take away from a fine win over Middlesbrough in the EFL Cup|url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fulham-five-things-take-away-11795918|publisher=Get West London|date=24 August 2016|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Slavisa Jokanovic rues missed chances after Fulham bow out of EFL Cup to Bristol City|url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/slavisa-jokanovic-rues-missed-chances-11920762|publisher=Get West London|date=22 September 2016|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> At the end of the 2016\u201317 season, he was offered a new contract by the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fulham's Scott Parker in talks over a new deal as club announce released list|url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fulhams-scott-parker-talks-over-13096877|publisher=Get West London|date=26 May 2017|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n===AC Horsens===\nHowever, instead of signing a new contract and pursue to leave the club over first team football, Joronen left Fulham to join Danish side [[AC Horsens]], signing a two-year contract on 10 July 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=AC Horsens handler igen: Henter Championship-keeper|url=https://www.bt.dk/fodbold/ac-horsens-handler-igen-henter-championship-keeper|publisher=BT.dk|language=Danish|date=10 July 2017|accessdate=21 October 2017}}<br>{{cite news|title=Fulham goalkeeper pens emotional goodbye message to fans|url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/fulham-goalkeeper-pens-emotional-goodbye-13307230|publisher=BBC Sport|date=10 July 2017|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nJoronen made his AC Horsens debut in the opening game of the season, in a 2\u20131 win over [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF Aarhus]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.achorsens.dk/sejr-i-saesonens-foerste-kamp|title=Sejr i s\u00e6sonens f\u00f8rste kamp|publisher=AC Horsens|language=Danish|date=14 July 2017|accessdate=21 October 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021195934/http://www.achorsens.dk/sejr-i-saesonens-foerste-kamp|archivedate=21 October 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 4 August 2017, he kept his first clean sheet for the side, in a 1\u20130 win over [[Silkeborg IF|Silkeborg]], a win saw the club go at the top of the table.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.achorsens.dk/sejr-i-saesonens-foerste-kamp|title=Sejr i s\u00e6sonens f\u00f8rste kamp|publisher=AC Horsens|language=Danish|date=4 August 2017|accessdate=21 October 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021195934/http://www.achorsens.dk/sejr-i-saesonens-foerste-kamp|archivedate=21 October 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===FC Copenhagen===\nOn 15 December 2017, it was announced that Joronen will join [[FC Copenhagen|Copenhagen]] in the summer of 2018 for a fee of \u20ac875,000. He has signed a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fck.dk/en/news/fc-copenhagen-sign-jesse-joronen|title=F.C. COPENHAGEN SIGN JESSE JORONEN|website=fck.dk|date=15 December 2017|accessdate=30 January 2019}}</ref> He made his competitive debut on 23 July 2018, playing the entirety of a 3\u20130 league victory over [[Hobro IK|Hobro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/07/23/denmark/superliga/hobro-ik/fc-kobenhavn/2790418/|title=Hobro vs. Kobenhavn \u2013 23 July 2018 \u2013 Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com|accessdate=30 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nHaving represented Finland at [[Finland national under-17 football team|U17]], [[Finland national under-19 football team|U19]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2011/october/28/joronen-called-up |title=Joronen Called-Up |publisher=Fulham F.C. |accessdate=27 December 2014 |date=26 August 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141227191213/http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2011/october/28/joronen-called-up |archivedate=27 December 2014 |url-status=unfit }}</ref> and [[Finland national under-21 football team|U21]] level,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2011/august/26/joronen-called-up |title=Joronen Called-Up |publisher=Fulham F.C. |accessdate=27 December 2014 |date=26 August 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141227191206/http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2011/august/26/joronen-called-up |archivedate=27 December 2014 |url-status=unfit }}</ref> Joronen was called up to the senior squad and made his debut for [[Finland national football team|Finland]] in the [[2013 King's Cup]] against [[Thailand national football team|Thailand]] on 24 January 2013.<ref name=\"intl\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{Expand Section|date=October 2017}}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Copenhagen'''\n*[[Danish Superliga]]: [[2018\u201319 Danish Superliga|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://cphpost.dk/news/sports/fc-copenhagen-are-danish-champions.html|title=FC Copenhagen are Danish champions|newspaper=[[The Copenhagen Post]]|date=6 May 2019|accessdate=7 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*[http://www.achorsens.dk/node/10500?width=500&height=400&iframe=true Jesse Joronen profile] at [[AC Horsens]]\n\n{{Brescia Calcio squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Joronen, Jesse}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Finnish footballers]]\n[[Category:Finland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Finland under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Finland youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Fulham F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Maidenhead United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Cambridge United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:FC Lahti players]]\n[[Category:Accrington Stanley F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Stevenage F.C. players]]\n[[Category:AC Horsens players]]\n[[Category:F.C. Copenhagen players]]\n[[Category:Brescia Calcio players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:Danish Superliga players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Finnish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Finnish expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers who have scored]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Finnish professional footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Jesse Joronen\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Jesse Pekka Joronen\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|3|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Rautj\u00e4rvi]], [[Finland]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.97}}\n| position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub = [[Brescia Calcio|Brescia]]\n| clubnumber = 1\n| youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20132009\n| youthclubs1 = Simpeleen Urheilijat\n| youthyears2 = 2009\n| youthclubs2 = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]\n| years1 = 2009\u20132017\n| clubs1 = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]\n| caps1 = 4\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2012\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Maidenhead United F.C.|Maidenhead United]] (loan)\n| caps2 = 8\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2013\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Cambridge United F.C.|Cambridge United]] (loan)\n| caps3 = 0\n| goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2013\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[FC Lahti]] (loan)\n| caps4 = 18\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2014\n| clubs5 = \u2192 [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] (loan)\n| caps5 = 4\n| goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2015\u20132016\n| clubs6 = \u2192 [[Stevenage F.C.|Stevenage]] (loan)\n| caps6 = 10\n| goals6 = 1\n| clubs7 = [[AC Horsens]]\n| caps7 = 28\n| goals7 = 0\n| years7 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs8 = [[F.C. Copenhagen|Copenhagen]]\n| caps8 = 37\n| goals8 = 0\n| years8 = 2018\u20132019\n| clubs9 = [[Brescia Calcio|Brescia]]\n| caps9 = 8\n| goals9 = 0\n| years9 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalyears1 = 2009\n| nationalteam1 = [[Finland national under-17 football team|Finland U17]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 6\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2010\n| nationalteam2 = [[Finland national under-19 football team|Finland U19]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 1\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2011\u20132014\n| nationalteam3 = [[Finland national under-21 football team|Finland U21]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 11\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2013\u2013\n| nationalteam4 = [[Finland national football team|Finland]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 8\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| club-update = 27 October 2019\n| ntupdate = 8 July 2018\n}}\n'''Jesse Pekka Joronen''' (born 21 March 1993) is a [[Finland|Finnish]] [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Serie A]] club [[Brescia Calcio|Brescia]].<ref>[https://www.fck.dk/en/news/jesse-joronen-sold-brescia-calcio]\u201a fck.dk, 11 July 2019</ref> Joronen made his senior debut for [[Finland national football team|Finland]] in 2013.<ref name=\"intl\">{{cite news|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2013/january/24/joronens-finland-bow|title=Joronen's Finland Bow|date=24 January 2013|publisher=Fulham F.C.|accessdate=1 March 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Fulham===\nBorn and raised in the small town of Simpele located near the Russian border, Joronen joined [[Fulham F.C. Academy|Fulham Academy]] in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/Club/News/NewsArticles/2010/October/Joronen.aspx|title=Through The Ranks|publisher=Fulham Official Website|accessdate=19 April 2014|date=20 October 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101022160532/http://www.fulhamfc.com/Club/News/NewsArticles/2010/October/Joronen.aspx|archivedate=22 October 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref> In June 2010, Joronen signed his first professional contract with the club, which will keep him until 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/Club/News/NewsArticles/2010/June/PlayerContractRound-Up.aspx|title=Player Contract Round-Up |publisher= Fulham FC|date=1 June 2010|accessdate=19 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110608065801/http://www.fulhamfc.com/Club/News/NewsArticles/2010/June/PlayerContractRound-Up.aspx|archivedate=8 June 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2012, Joronen signed a two-year extension with Fulham, that will keep him until 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Suomalaismaalivahti jatkosopimukseen Fulhamin kanssa|url=http://www.mtv.fi/sport/jalkapallo/valioliiga/artikkeli/suomalaismaalivahti-jatkosopimukseen-fulhamin-kanssa/4014396|publisher=MTV.fi|language=Finnish|date=15 May 2012|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> Six month later, on 25 October 2012, Joronen joined [[Maidenhead United F.C.|Maidenhead United]] on loan<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.maidenhead-advertiser.co.uk/Sport/Football/Maidenhead-Utd-FC/Maidenhead-United-FC-sign-international-keeper-from-Fulham-25102012.htm|title=Maidenhead United FC sign international keeper from Fulham|date=25 October 2012|publisher=Maidenhead Advertiser|accessdate=1 March 2013}}</ref> and in February 2013, Joronen was loaned to [[Cambridge United F.C.|Cambridge United]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/21545766|title=Fulham keeper Jesse Joronen joins Cambridge United|date=22 February 2013|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=1 March 2013}}</ref> Only a day later Joronen returned to Fulham after he refused to be named as a substitute for Cambridge.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Sport/Cambridge-United/Cambridge-United-1-Hereford-United-3-23022013.htm |title=Cambridge United 1 Hereford United 3 |date=23 February 2013 |publisher=Cambridge News |accessdate=1 March 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103051228/http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Sport/Cambridge-United/Cambridge-United-1-Hereford-United-3-23022013.htm |archivedate= 3 January 2014 }}</ref>\n\nAfter a loan spell at Maidenhead United, Joronen then move back to Finland, where he joined Veikkausliiga side [[FC Lahti]] on loan until August.<ref>{{cite news|title=Joronen Fulhamista FC Lahteen \u2013 \"Haluan kehitty\u00e4 pelaajana\"|url=http://yle.fi/urheilu/joronen_fulhamista_fc_lahteen_-_haluan_kehittya_pelaajana/6618714|publisher=Yle Sports|language=Finnish|date=5 March 2013|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> After making eighteen appearance for the club, which he established himself as a first choice goalkeeper, Joronen returned to his parent club in early August.<ref>{{cite news|title=Englantiin palannut Jesse Joronen: \"FC Lahti ansaitsisi pronssin\"|url=http://www.suomifutis.com/2013/10/englantiin-palannut-jesse-joronen-fc-lahti-ansaitsisi-pronssin/|publisher=Soumi Futis.com|language=Finnish|date=14 October 2013|accessdate=27 December 2014}}<br>{{cite news|title=FC Lahti menett\u00e4\u00e4 ykk\u00f6svahtinsa|url=https://www.is.fi/veikkausliiga/art-2000000643261.html|publisher=Ilta-Sanomat|language=Finnish|date=28 July 2013|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nAt the start of the 2014\u201315 season, Joronen signed a two-year contract with the club that kept him until 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=New Deal For Jesse |url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2014/july/07/new-deal-for-jesse |publisher=Fulham F.C. |date=7 July 2014 |accessdate=27 December 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141227172903/http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2014/july/07/new-deal-for-jesse |archivedate=December 27, 2014 |url-status=unfit }}</ref> He was then given his debut as the starting goalkeeper in Fulham's opening game in the [[Football League Championship|Championship]] against [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] on 9 August 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/28646535|title=Ipswich Town 2\u20131 Fulham|publisher=BBC Sport|date=9 August 2014|accessdate=21 November 2014}}</ref> After making three more appearance for the club, Joronen soon lost his first team place to [[Marcus Bettinelli]] and new goalkeeper signing, [[G\u00e1bor Kir\u00e1ly]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Fulham boss admits the club refused to buy a top keeper|url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/fulham-boss-admits-club-refused-7707322|publisher=Get West London|date=1 September 2014|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nJoronen joined [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] on loan for one month on 17 October 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29661972|title=Jesse Joronen: Fulham goalkeeper joins Accrington on loan|publisher=BBC Sport|date=17 October 2014|accessdate=21 November 2014}}</ref> Shortly after, he made his Accrington Stanley debut the next day, on 18 October 2014, starting in goal, in a 2\u20131 loss against Stevenage.<ref>{{cite news|title=FULL TIME: Stevenage 2 Accrington Stanley 1|url=http://www.lancashiretelegraph.co.uk/sport/11544716.FULL_TIME__Stevenage_2_Accrington_Stanley_1/|publisher=The Lancashire Telegraph|date=18 October 2014|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> However, after making three more appearance at Accrington Stanley whilst on loan, he returned early after dislocating his kneecap during a [[Football League Two|League Two]] match against [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Accrington Stanley captain Luke Joyce impressed with Shay McCartan's form|url=http://www.lancashiretelegraph.co.uk/sport/11577810.Accrington_Stanley_captain_Luke_Joyce_impressed_with_Shay_McCartan_s_form/|publisher=The Lancashire Telegraph|date=4 November 2014|accessdate=21 November 2014}}</ref> Then, it was announced that Joronen would be out for three to four months.<ref>{{cite news|title=Huuhkajavahti Jesse Joronen palaa kentille vasta ensi vuonna|url=http://www.sportti.com/uutinen.asp?CAT=3-3&ID=277013|publisher=Sportti.com|language=Finnish|date=3 November 2014|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 August 2015, Joronen signed for [[Stevenage F.C.|Stevenage]] on loan until January 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stevenage: Boro sign Jesse Joronen on loan from Fulham|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34078392|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 August 2015|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> He made his Stevenage debut two days later, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Super sub Hitchcock strikes to claim point at Dagenham and Redbridge|url=http://www.thecomet.net/sport/football/super-sub-hitchcock-strikes-to-claim-point-at-dagenham-and-redbridge-1-4213810|publisher=The Comet|date=29 August 2015|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> Joronen scored with a long-range clearance in a match against [[Wycombe Wanderers F.C.|Wycombe Wanderers]] on 17 October 2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/football-league/goalkeeper-jesse-joronen-scores-freak-long-range-goal-for-stevenage-from-just-outside-his-own-a6698206.html|title=Goalkeeper Jesse Joronen scores freak long-range goal for Stevenage from just outside his own penalty box|publisher=The Independent|date=17 October 2015|accessdate=17 October 2015}}</ref> He then kept his first clean sheet in a 3\u20130 win over [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]] in the first round of the FA Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stevenage 3 \u2013 0 Gillingham|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34685654|publisher=BBC Sport|date=7 November 2015|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> However, after making eleven appearance for the side, Joronen suffered an injury during the match against Gillingham and subsequently returned to his parent club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Yeovil Town preview: We have to be cautious but we are still going out to win this \"six-pointer\" says Teddy Sheringham|url=http://www.thecomet.net/stevenage-fc/yeovil-town-preview-we-have-to-be-cautious-but-we-are-still-going-out-to-win-this-six-pointer-says-teddy-sheringham-1-4310479|publisher=The Comet|date=13 November 2015|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> After returning to his parent club, Joronen signed a contract extension, keeping him until 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2016/may/12/jesse-joronen-extends-fulham-stay|title=Jesse Extends Fulham Stay|publisher=Fulham F.C.|accessdate=21 October 2017|date=12 May 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021193709/http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2016/may/12/jesse-joronen-extends-fulham-stay|archivedate=October 21, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2016\u201317 season, Joronen was featured three times in the EFL Cup, being the first choice goalkeeper ahead of Bettinelli.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fulham and the five things to take away from a fine win over Middlesbrough in the EFL Cup|url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fulham-five-things-take-away-11795918|publisher=Get West London|date=24 August 2016|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Slavisa Jokanovic rues missed chances after Fulham bow out of EFL Cup to Bristol City|url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/slavisa-jokanovic-rues-missed-chances-11920762|publisher=Get West London|date=22 September 2016|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref> At the end of the 2016\u201317 season, he was offered a new contract by the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fulham's Scott Parker in talks over a new deal as club announce released list|url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fulhams-scott-parker-talks-over-13096877|publisher=Get West London|date=26 May 2017|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n===AC Horsens===\nHowever, instead of signing a new contract and pursue to leave the club over first team football, Joronen left Fulham to join Danish side [[AC Horsens]], signing a two-year contract on 10 July 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=AC Horsens handler igen: Henter Championship-keeper|url=https://www.bt.dk/fodbold/ac-horsens-handler-igen-henter-championship-keeper|publisher=BT.dk|language=Danish|date=10 July 2017|accessdate=21 October 2017}}<br>{{cite news|title=Fulham goalkeeper pens emotional goodbye message to fans|url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/fulham-goalkeeper-pens-emotional-goodbye-13307230|publisher=BBC Sport|date=10 July 2017|accessdate=21 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nJoronen made his AC Horsens debut in the opening game of the season, in a 2\u20131 win over [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF Aarhus]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.achorsens.dk/sejr-i-saesonens-foerste-kamp|title=Sejr i s\u00e6sonens f\u00f8rste kamp|publisher=AC Horsens|language=Danish|date=14 July 2017|accessdate=21 October 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021195934/http://www.achorsens.dk/sejr-i-saesonens-foerste-kamp|archivedate=21 October 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 4 August 2017, he kept his first clean sheet for the side, in a 1\u20130 win over [[Silkeborg IF|Silkeborg]], a win saw the club go at the top of the table.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.achorsens.dk/sejr-i-saesonens-foerste-kamp|title=Sejr i s\u00e6sonens f\u00f8rste kamp|publisher=AC Horsens|language=Danish|date=4 August 2017|accessdate=21 October 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021195934/http://www.achorsens.dk/sejr-i-saesonens-foerste-kamp|archivedate=21 October 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===FC Copenhagen===\n\nOn 15 December 2017, it was announced that Joronen will join [[FC Copenhagen|Copenhagen]] in the summer of 2018 for a fee of \u20ac875,000. He has signed a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fck.dk/en/news/fc-copenhagen-sign-jesse-joronen|title=F.C. COPENHAGEN SIGN JESSE JORONEN|website=fck.dk|date=15 December 2017|accessdate=30 January 2019}}</ref> He made his competitive debut on 23 July 2018, playing the entirety of a 3-0 league victory over [[Hobro IK|Hobro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/07/23/denmark/superliga/hobro-ik/fc-kobenhavn/2790418/|title=Hobro vs. Kobenhavn \u2013 23 July 2018 \u2013 Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com|accessdate=30 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nHaving represented Finland at [[Finland national under-17 football team|U17]], [[Finland national under-19 football team|U19]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2011/october/28/joronen-called-up |title=Joronen Called-Up |publisher=Fulham F.C. |accessdate=27 December 2014 |date=26 August 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141227191213/http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2011/october/28/joronen-called-up |archivedate=December 27, 2014 |url-status=unfit }}</ref> and [[Finland national under-21 football team|U21]] level,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2011/august/26/joronen-called-up |title=Joronen Called-Up |publisher=Fulham F.C. |accessdate=27 December 2014 |date=26 August 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141227191206/http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2011/august/26/joronen-called-up |archivedate=December 27, 2014 |url-status=unfit }}</ref> Joronen was called up to the senior squad and made his debut for [[Finland national football team|Finland]] in the [[2013 King's Cup]] against [[Thailand national football team|Thailand]] on 24 January 2013.<ref name=\"intl\"/>\n\n==Career Statistics==\n{{Expand Section|date=October 2017}}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Copenhagen'''\n*[[Danish Superliga]]: [[2018\u201319 Danish Superliga|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://cphpost.dk/news/sports/fc-copenhagen-are-danish-champions.html|title=FC Copenhagen are Danish champions|newspaper=[[The Copenhagen Post]]|date=6 May 2019|accessdate=7 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*[http://www.achorsens.dk/node/10500?width=500&height=400&iframe=true Jesse Joronen profile] at [[AC Horsens]]\n\n{{Brescia Calcio squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Joronen, Jesse}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Finnish footballers]]\n[[Category:Finland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Finland under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Finland youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Fulham F.C. players]]\n[